#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:355
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adjusting the Profile"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:356
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When adding a distribution (see <xref linkend=\"sec.prep.makeavail."
"zpxe_cobbler.add_distro\"/>) a profile with the corresponding "
"<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable> is automatically generated. Use the "
"following command to make a few required adjustments:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cobbler distro edit \\\n"
"--name=<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable><co xml:id=\"cobbler.profile.name"
"\"/> --os-version=sles10<co xml:id=\"cobbler.profile.os\"/> --ksmeta=\"\"<co "
"xml:id=\"cobbler.profile.meta\"/>\n"
"--kopts=\"install=http://cobbler.example.com/cobbler/ks_mirror/"
"<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable>\"<co xml:id=\"cobbler.profile.opts\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:367
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identifier for the profile. Use the same string as specified when having "
"added the distribution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:373
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Operating system version. Distribution to which the profile should apply. "
"You must use the string specified with <option>--"
"name=<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable></option> in the importing step "
"here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Option needed for templating kickstart files. Not used for &suse;, so set to "
"an empty value as specified in the example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Space-separated list of Kernel parameters. Should include at least the "
"<literal>install</literal> parameter as shown in the example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:395
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Adding Systems</title>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:396
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The last step that is required is to add systems to the Cobbler server. A "
"system addition needs to be done for every &zseries; guest that should boot "
"via zPXE. Guests are identified via their z/VM user ID (in the following "
"example, an ID called <quote>linux01</quote> is assumed). Note that this ID "
"needs to be a lowercase string. To add a system, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cobbler system add --name=linux01 --hostname=linux01.example.com \\\n"
"--profile=<replaceable>IDENTIFIER</replaceable> --interface=qdio \\\n"
"--ip-address=&wsIVip; --subnet=&subnetII;.255 --netmask=&subnetmask; \\\n"
"--name-servers=&dnsip; --name-servers-search=&exampledomain; \\\n"
"--gateway=&routerintipII; --kopts=\"<replaceable>KERNEL_OPTIONS</replaceable>"
"\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the <option>--kopts</option> option you can specify the kernel and "
"installation parameters you would normally specify in the parmfile. The "
"parameters are entered as a space-separated list in the form of "
"<replaceable>PARAMETER1=VALUE1 PARAMETER2=VALUE2</replaceable>. The "
"installer will prompt you for missing parameters. For a completely automated "
"installation you need to specify all parameters for networking, DASDs and "
"provide an &ay; file. The following shows an example for a guest equipped "
"with an OSA interface using the same network parameters as above."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"--kopts=\" \\\n"
"AutoYaST=http://&exampledomainip;.5/autoinst.xml \\\n"
"Hostname=linux01.example.com \\\n"
"Domain=&exampledomain; \\\n"
"HostIP=&wsIVip; \\\n"
"Gateway=&routerintipII; \\\n"
"Nameserver=&dnsip; \\\n"
"Searchdns=&exampledomain; \\\n"
"InstNetDev=osa; \\\n"
"Netmask=&subnetmask; \\\n"
"Broadcast=&subnetII;.255 \\\n"
"OsaInterface=qdio \\\n"
"Layer2=0 \\\n"
"PortNo=0 \\\n"
"ReadChannel=0.0.0700 \\\n"
"WriteChannel=0.0.0701 \\\n"
"DataChannel=0.0.0702 \\\n"
"DASD=600\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:419
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing from DVD or Flash Disk of the HMC"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:420
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To install SUSE Linux Enterprise Server on IBM z Systems servers, usually a "
"network installation source is needed. However, in certain environments, it "
"could occur that this requirement cannot be fulfilled. With SUSE Linux "
"Enterprise Server 11 SP2, you can use the existing DVD or the flash disk of "
"the Hardware Management Console (HMC) as an installation source for "
"installation on an LPAR."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To install from the media in the DVD or the flash disk of the HMC, proceed "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:434
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Add</para>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:438
#, no-c-format
msgid "install=hmc:/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"to the <filename>parmfile</filename> (see <xref linkend=\"sec.appdendix.parm"
"\"/>) or kernel options."
