#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1099
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, you are prompted for details on the installation server, such as "
"the IP address, the directory containing the installation data, and login "
"credentials. Once all required data is entered, the installation system "
"loads."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Connecting to the &productname; Installation System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After having loaded the installation system, linuxrc wants to know what type "
"of display you want to use to control the installation procedure. Possible "
"choices are <literal>X11</literal> (X Window System), <literal>VNC</literal> "
"(Virtual Network Computing protocol), <literal>SSH</literal> (text mode or "
"X11 installation via Secure Shell), or <literal>ASCII Console</literal>. "
"Selecting <literal>VNC</literal> or <literal>SSH</literal> is recommended."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When selecting the latter (<literal>ASCII Console</literal>), &yast; will be "
"started in text mode and you can perform the installation directly within "
"your terminal. See <xref linkend=\"cha.yast.text\"/> for instructions on how "
"to use &yast; in text mode. Using the <literal>ASCII Console</literal> is "
"only useful when installing into LPAR."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminal Emulation for ASCII Console"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1128
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To be able to work with &yast; in text mode, it needs to run in a terminal "
"with VT220/Linux emulation (also called <literal>ASCII console</literal>). "
"You cannot use &yast; in a 3270 terminal, for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1135
#, no-c-format
msgid "Initiating the Installation for VNC"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the installation option <literal>VNC</literal> has been chosen, the "
"VNC server starts. A short note displayed in the console provides "
"information about which IP address and display number is needed for a "
"connection with vncviewer. Alternatively, a URL is given here for entry into "
"your Java-enabled browser to connect to the installation system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start a VNC client application on your client system. Either use vncviewer "
"or the VNC Java client and a Java-enabled Web browser."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter the IP address and the display number of the &productname; "
"installation system when prompted to do so."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you connect via a Java-enabled browser, enter a URL containing the IP "
"address of the installation system and the appropriate port number in the "
"format:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1162
#, no-c-format
msgid "http://&lt;IP address of installation system&gt;:5801/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the connection has been established, start installing &productname; "
"with &yast;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1173
#, no-c-format
msgid "Initiating the Installation for the X Window System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1175
#, no-c-format
msgid "X Authentication Mechanism"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The direct installation with the X Window System relies on a primitive "
"authentication mechanism based on host names. This mechanism is disabled on "
"current &productname; versions. Installation with SSH or VNC is preferred."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that the X server allows the client (the system that is installed) "
"to connect. Set the variable "
"<command>DISPLAYMANAGER_XSERVER_TCP_PORT_6000_OPEN=\"yes\"</command> in the "
"file <filename>/etc/sysconfig/displaymanager</filename>. Then restart the X "
"server and allow client binding to the server using <command>xhost &lt;"
"client IP address&gt;</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When prompted at the installation system, enter the IP address of the "
"machine running the X server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1201
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wait until &yast; opens then start the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Initiating the Installation for SSH"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To connect to an installation system with the name <literal>&exampleclient;</"
"literal> using SSH, execute <command>ssh -X &exampleclient;</command>. If "
"your workstation runs on Microsoft Windows, use the SSH and telnet client "
"and terminal emulator Putty which is available from <link xlink:href="
"\"http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/\"></link>. Set "
"<guimenu>Enable X11 forwarding</guimenu> in Putty under <menuchoice> "
"<guimenu>Connection</guimenu> <guimenu>SSH</guimenu> <guimenu>X11</guimenu> "
"</menuchoice>. If you use another operating system, execute <command>ssh -X "
"&exampleclient;</command> to connect to an installation system with the name "
"<systemitem>&exampleclient;</systemitem>. X-Forwarding over SSH is supported "
"if you have a local X server available. Otherwise, &yast; provides a text "
"interface over ncurses."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A login prompt appears. Enter <literal>root</literal> and log in with your "
"password. Enter <command>yast.ssh</command> to start &yast;. &yast; then "
"guides you through the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Proceed with the detailed description of the installation procedure that can "
"be found in <xref linkend=\"cha.inst\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1237
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &productname; Boot Procedure on IBM &zseries;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The boot process for &slsa; 10 and 11 followed the scheme provided below. "
"For in-depth information refer to the documentation provided at <link xlink:"
"href=\"http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/linux/linux390/documentation_suse."
"html\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1245
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provide the Kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Provide or create an initrd for the given Kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provide the correct paths for the initrd and the Kernel in <filename>/etc/"
"zipl.conf</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install the configuration provided by <filename>/etc/zipl.conf</filename> to "
"the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With &slsa; 12 the way &productname; is booted on IBM &zseries; has changed. "
"Several reasons led to this change:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alignment with other architectures: From an administrative point of view "
"&slsa; systems should behave the same on all architectures."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Btrfs: The zipl boot loader is technically incompatible with Btrfs, the new "
"default root file system for &slsa; (see <xref linkend=\"sec.filesystems."
"major.btrfs\"/> for details)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Support for system rollbacks with Snapper: Snapper, in combination with "
"Btrfs, provides bootable system snapshots which can be used for system "
"rollbacks (see <xref linkend=\"cha.snapper\"/> for details)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For those reasons, starting with &slsa; 12, &grub; replaces zipl on IBM "
"&productname; for &zseries;. &grub; on the &amd64;/&intel64; architecture "
"includes device drivers on the firmware level to access the file system. On "
"the mainframe there is no firmware and adding <literal>ccw</literal> to "
"&grub; would not only be a huge task, but also would be a reimplementation "
"of zipl in &grub;. Therefore &productname; uses a two-stage approach:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1304
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stage One:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_prep_zseries_prep_i.xml:1306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A separate partition containing the Kernel and an initrd is mounted to "
"<filename>/boot/zipl</filename> (somewhat similar to <filename>/boot/efi</"
"filename> on UEFI platforms). This Kernel and the initrd are loaded via zipl "
